title: 1989 Matchroom League
text:
The 1989 <a href="Premier%20League%20Snooker">Matchroom League</a> was a professional non-<a href="Snooker%20world%20rankings">ranking</a> <a href="snooker">snooker</a> tournament that was played from January to May 1989.
<a href="Steve%20Davis">Steve Davis</a> topped the table and won the tournament. <a href="Cliff%20Thorburn">Cliff Thorburn</a> recorded a maximum break in his match against <a href="Jimmy%20White">Jimmy White</a>. 
League phase.
If points were level then match wins, followed by most frames won determined their positions. If two players had an identical record then the result in their match determined their positions. If that ended 4–4 then the player who got to four first was higher.
